newspaper die welt said 
it quoted wolff as saying the money was legally acquired and 
should be treated like the savings of other east germans 
west german marks will become the currency of east germany on 
july 2 when the nations merge their economies a key step in 
unification 
under a formula for replacing the nearly worthless east german 
mark older people would have savings of up to 6000 marks 
converted at a 1to1 rate and amounts higher than that at a 
2to1 rate 
honeckers money would be valued at 153000 west german marks 
90270 
honecker and other officials of the former communist regime 
toppled in october were taken to a police hospital in east berlin 
on may 28 
