an american airlines jetliner with 70 people 
on board made an emergency landing in omaha after losing cabin 
pressure but no one was injured officials said 
i think everybody was pretty calm said jeremy turk 33 a 
passenger on flight 840 from oakland to chicago it was quite 
uneventful 
the mcdonnell douglas super 80 carrying 64 passengers and a 
sixmember crew made the unscheduled but safe landing at eppley 
airfield at 1150 am cdt officials said 
passengers remained in the twinengine jet for about an hour 
before entering the airport and were given boarding passes for 
another flight to chicago 
the cause of the loss in cabin pressure was not known said 
american airlines spokesman al becker 
becker did not know the planes altitude when the problem 
developed 
most of the people on the jet were asleep when pressure was 
lost several passengers said 
all of a sudden it was ding ding and the masks fell down 
in front of my face said joe sivertsen 21 i woke up and 
said oh thats nice now whats happening 
it was handled very well by the flight crew turk said 
