<TEXT>
valerian s rybar known as the worlds most 
expensive interior designer has died of prostate cancer he was 71 
rybar internationally known for creating opulent rooms and 
extravagant party designs died saturday at his manhattan home 
said his partner jeanfrancois daigre 
rybars clients included nicholas and genvieve dupont samuel 
and mitzi newhouse pierre and sao schlumberger christina onassis 
and stavros niarchos 
he designed many of the furniture pieces and rugs he used 
employing artisans from all over the world he often chose opulent 
fabrics like satins trimmed with gold thread or red velvet 
mirrors and steel were rybar signatures 
the real luxury today is not that one incredible piece of 
furniture he once said its perfect cooking and grooming 
facilities and perfect storage 
the native of yugoslavia began his career as a trainee at the 
lord amp taylor department store in new york soon after he quit he 
designed a headdress for an opera singer 
cosmetics company founder elizabeth arden saw it and took him 
under her wing daigre said 
he stayed at arden for three years then began working on party 
designs and soon was hired by some of his clients to help them with 
their homes 
daigre joined rybar in 1968 their company had offices in new 
york and paris 
there are no survivors 
</TEXT>
