a woman who angered neighbors and got in 
trouble with zoning authorities for taking in homeless mothers said 
tuesday she would close down the operation and seek approval to run 
it as a shelter 
in a letter to this southwestern connecticut towns zoning 
enforcment officer donna russell said she was ready to comply with 
the dec 15 order banning her from operating her lakefront home as 
a shelter 
russell wrote donald murray that she has agreed to go along with 
the order on the understanding that she and her 18yearold son 
daniel will not be fined and that no further action will be taken 
against them if she complies within a reasonable time 
last week officials warned that russells son the legal owner 
of the house faced arrest on a misdemeanor charge of violating 
local zoning ordinances if the matter remained unresolved 
russell asked in her letter that she be given time to find 
alternate housing for the two women currently living in her home 
the town issued its december ceaseanddesist order after local 
officials concluded that russell was operating a homeless shelter 
in violation of local zoning law the law requires that 
threequarters of the people living in a single family dwelling be 
related by blood marriage or adoption 
in her letter russell wrote i still believe that the towns 
actions against me were unfair and unconstitutional 
