<TEXT>
fbi agents would have more leeway to shoot at 
suspects under a proposed new policy sources say 
agents could shoot fleeing suspects of violent crimes who are 
armed and considered likely to commit another crime said the 
sources who spoke on condition of anonymity 
deadly force also could be used if the agent had a reasonable 
belief that the suspect could not be arrested without firing shots 
under current policy fbi agents may use deadly force only in 
selfdefense or to protect the life of another person 
the new policy has been under study since 1985 when the supreme 
court held that police officers could shoot a fleeing armed 
suspect if the officers believed the person posed a threat to 
public safety said the sources 
the increase in drugrelated violence prompted the drafting of 
the new policy said the sources 
the fbi is awaiting clearance from attorney general dick 
thornburgh before making an announcement of the policy change said 
the sources 
