the fighting apparently broke out when a tamil man told rebels 
of the dominant tamil militia the tigers that he had been 
assaulted by a sinhalese policemen at the batticaloa police station 
on sunday officials said 
the tigers on monday ordered policemen out of the station and 
took command 
the tigers took virtual control of the countrys northeastern 
districts after indian peacekeeping forces withdrew in march 
president ranasinghe premadasas government which has been 
negotiating with the tigers for the past year requested the 
indians departure 
at least 11000 people including 1200 indian soldiers have 
been killed in the tamil war since it started in 1983 
another 6000 have been killed since 1987 in a backlash to tamil 
demands whipped up by ultranationalist sinhalese guerrillas 
