democratic forces and of an anarchist group say sundays elections 
were manipulated but most foreign observers said they saw little 
or no wrongdoing 
the opposition pledged tuesday to rally behind candidates not 
associated with the socialist party in the runoffs in 81 
constituencies in a lastditch bid to gain control of parliament 
