in women under the guise of legitimate marriage 
the measure outlaws the solicitation or inducement of 
filipino women to become members of any club or association whose 
objective is to match women for marriage to foreign nationals 
either on a mailorder basis or through personal introductions for 
a fee 
it also bans the printing and distribution of material promoting 
the practice violators could face up to eight years in jail and 
870 in fines 
the mailorder bride business is a relatively new phenomenon 
in our society but its perpetrators are many said mrs aquino 
they are able to carry out their pernicious trade through the use 
of the media for personal profit 
mrs aquino said many poor young women from remote villges are 
lured through sweet talk and grandiose promises by the 
mailorder bride businesses 
