calls for faster and more radical steps to make the switch from 
central planning to a market economy 
we cant stretch the elastic we have to begin work now 
alexei boiko chairman of an economic reform commission told 
parliamentary deputies urging the speeding up of the program 
the draft resolution would instruct the government to cut 
spending immediately on the military and the state bureaucracy 
