commissions and is fairly objective and allows us to work 
further he said but he said it would be difficult to complete 
all the laws and practical measures by the autumn deadline 
todays proposal did not address the ryzhkov plans price 
increases for most consumer products which are due to take effect 
in january the ryzhkov plan was criticized for raising prices 
without freeing enough goods and prices from government control to 
allow a true transition to a market economy 
particularly unpopular was the proposal to at least double the 
price of bread the staple of the soviet diet currently bread is 
extremely cheap at about 30 cents a loaf 
