congressional republicans on restricting grants awarded by the 
national endowment for the arts a congressman said wednesday 
rep paul henry dmich said after a meeting with nea chairman 
paul frohnmayer that the administration had dropped its previous 
strong opposition to any type of content restrictions or standards 
in a bill to extend the life of the agency 
the change comes as congressional concern is increasing over 
federal subsidies going to arts projects that some consider 
obscene pornographic or sacrilegious 
i think weve reached a point that if youre going to rescue 
the nea you have to speak forthrightly about what receives public 
support henry said the members have gotten so much mail on 
