is listing and crews might have to pump water into the holds to 
keep the vessel balanced the ships rear has dropped more than 60 
feet and remained awash today 
were feeling fairly confident at this point but were not 
going to really breathe easy until the oil is back in a terminal 
petty officer todd nelson said 
