connection with payments for helping build the plant 
hippenstiel admitted not paying taxes on 117 million on 
profits from his transactions he said however that he did not 
keep the money for himself but used it to ensure the project in 
rabta would be completed 
the libyan plant scandal first came to light in december 1988 
when the united states government charged that west german 
companies were providing massive assistance for construction of a 
chemical factory capable of producing poison gas 
