fiscal year 1991 
the administration decided to move about 6 million from 
university nuclear engineering research programs and scholarships 
to place greater emphasis on precollege science and 
mathematics programs he said 
there is a growing consensus that one of the most serious 
problems facing the nation over the next 10 years is the declining 
number of young americans including women and minorities 
interested in pursuing careers in science and engineering decker 
said 
doe is uniquely positioned to provide major assistance to the 
national effort to strengthen science and engineering education 
he added 
the energy department has traditionally supported science 
education at the graduate and postdoctoral levels its university 
research in fiscal year 1990 totals about 480 million 
richard stephens director of does university and industry 
division said the department had worked closely with 57 
universities that have nuclear engineering programs providing 
degrees ranging from bachelors to doctorates 
there are 36 active projects with an average of three graduate 
students each receiving the scholarships stephens stressed that 
none of the current scholarship recipients will be affected by the 
budget switch because for each of the three years of the program 
threeyear awards were granted 
