cuellar said wednesday he will dispatch a delegation to the 
israelioccupied territories to investigate violence including 
alleged abuses of palestinians 
he said the group would go early next week 
the un chiefs announcement came one day after israels new 
conservative government invited him to send a special envoy but 
perez de cuellar said he was already planning to send a team 
un officials speaking on condition of anonymity said the 
delegation might depart for israel as early as monday night the 
group will be headed by jeanclaude aime a director in the un 
secretariat 
un officials said the secretarygeneral had been planning for 
several weeks to send an investigative team to the west bank and 
gaza strip where violence has escalated recently 
on tuesday evening perez de cuellar summoned israeli ambassador 
johanan bein to inform him of the plans bein told reporters 
beforehand that israel would initiate an invitation to the un 
team 
he later said israel would fully cooperate with the delegation 
