<TEXT>
a threemonthold banana battle has 
ended with united brands agreeing to let the irishenglish firm 
fyffes buy honduran bananas and gain a toehold in the central 
american country for the first time 
the agreement between new yorkbased united brands and more than 
600 independent producers affects about 1 million of the 47 million 
boxes of bananas honduras exports annually but the dispute 
ballooned to far greater proportions 
united brands which had exported all of the bananas from the 
independent producers will buy 60 percent until march 31 1991 
