<TEXT>
top officials of us financial exchanges and 
several major accounting and securities firms have joined forces 
with the securities and exchange commission to determine the best 
ways of helping the new free market economies of eastern europe 
in its first gathering tuesday the secs emerging markets 
advisory committee mapped preliminary strategy and planned smaller 
working groups 
it is the right thing for the united states to give the 
benefit of our knowledge and our experience to these other 
countries sec chairman richard c breeden told the blue ribbon 
panel 
the group included michael minikes senior managing director of 
investment bank bear stearns american stock exchange chairman 
james r jones joseph hardiman president of the national 
association of securities dealers inc and leo melamed head of 
the chicago mercantile exchange 
breeden proposed setting up the panel in march and has sought an 
active role in helping easter europe emerge from decades of 
socialism 
he will travel to hungary later this month to speak at the 
official reopening of the budapest stock exchange dormant since 
1948 when the communists came to power he also has met with 
polish hungarian and soviet officials in recent months 
breeden noted that foreign officials who have sought sec 
assistance and advice do not have time for lengthy reports and 
studies 
they want assistance that is practical and concrete he 
advised the panelists 
also addressing the group was oscar espinosa villareal 
president of mexicos national securities commission and michael 
j boskin chairman of the council of economic advisers 
we must not only work to develop the markets that already 
exist but we must also provide the necessary priority to the 
markets that do not yet exist specifically we must focus on the 
countries of eastern europe in their process of incorporation to a 
market economy espinosa villareal said 
a surprise guest was wieslaw rozlucki an adviser to polands 
finance ministry who was in washington to attend a world bank 
conference 
