american express co plans to issue more than 
800 million worth of stock to help finance its shoring up of 
troubled investment banking subsidiary shearson lehman hutton inc 
the travel and charge card company said tuesday would issue 27 
million shares of common stock which would bring in about 825 
million at current market prices before selling costs 
most of the proceeds will be used to eliminate 500 million in 
shortterm debt american express took on in march when it bought 
750 million worth of shearson preferred stock 
american express has injected more than 1 billion into shearson 
in recent months and is taking full control in an effort to 
revitalize the struggling wall street house 
american express already owns 60 percent of shearson the 
nations secondlargest brokerage the company said it expects to 
buy the remainder of shearson in the third quarter 
nippon life insurance co will buy 300 million of the stock 
offering the purchase is intended to replace the japanese 
companys stake in shearson that is being sold to american express 
in the buyout american express said in a statement 
after its purchase of the new stock nippon lifes total 
investment in american express will be less than 5 percent of the 
companys nearly 447 million shares 
nippon life plans to pay the lesser of the public offering price 
or 3096 a share for not less than 969 million shares 
american express closed at 3037 tuesday down 25 cents in 
new york stock exchange trading the offering was announced after 
the stock market closed 
the offering is subject to completion of the merger between 
american express and shearson and regulatory approvals officials 
expect the offering to be made in early july 
shearson lost 915 million in the first three months of the 
year a record in the securities industry it announced a 
restructuring earlier this month that will consolidate the firm 
into two divisions instead of four 
the divisions will be shearson lehman brothers for individual 
investing and asset management and lehman brothers for investment 
banking and capital markets activities the full firm will be known 
as shearson lehman brothers inc 
american express began taking charge of its ailing subsidiary 
late last year the changes have included replacing chairman peter 
a cohen who led shearson through a large expansion in the 1980s 
with howard l clark jr a top american express official 
american express also has pumped capital into shearson and 
engineeried a major restructuring that has resulted in more than 
2000 layoffs 
