million project to jointly develop the vehicles for european and 
north american production in the mid1990s chrysler spokesman tom 
houston said the joint project was no longer attractive 
economically 
the collapse of the deal comes as chrysler and other automakers 
worldwide eye economic developments in western and eastern europe 
which represent the worlds biggest auto market 
analyst chuck brady said he was surprised by the announcement 
i dont see what has changed to make it uneconomical said 
brady of oppenheimer amp co in new york it doesnt make any 
sense 
last week general motors corp announced a joint venture with 
volga auto works of the soviet union gm executives said the 
project to provide fuel system components represented their 
entrance to a potentially huge marketplace 
although houston said the planned joint venture was no longer 
attractive he indicated chrysler is considering developing the 
vehicle codenamed jj by itself or with another partner 
chrysler intends to continue with the jj project and is 
reviewing various implementation alternatives houston said 
declining to disclose details 
