<TEXT>
smithkline beecham has filed a law suit 
accusing two competitors of lying to obtain government approval for 
generic versions of smithklines antihypertension drug dyazide 
bolar pharmaceutical co inc of copiague ny and vitarine 
pharmaceuticals inc of springfield gardens ny both 
manufactured and sold generic versions of dyazide until the past 
year when allegations of false reports to the food and drug 
administration surfaced 
the suit filed in federal court tuesday accuses bolar of 
falsifying evidence that its generic drug is dyazides 
bioequivalent that is the generic drug achieves the same effect 
in the same dosage 
the suit accuses bolar of backdating testing studies to make it 
appear the companys tests were performed on a batch of dyazide 
when in fact they were performed on a batch that was not prepared 
according to federal procedures 
bolar took its generic version of the drug off the market in 
january after acknowledging that the company had faked lab tests to 
win fda approval 
vitarine when taking their version off the market in june 1989 
admitted its substituted dyazide for its product in tests required 
to win fda approval 
smithkline was injured because those schemes and 
representations enabled the companies to obtain fda approval 
to sell their generic versions of dyazide to persons who otherwise 
would have bought dyazide from smithkline the suit claims 
dyazide is one of smithklines bestselling products with 
annual sales exceeding 300 million in 1987 according to the suit 
in 1988 after the generic substitutes entered the market sales 
fell to 153 million 
the suit characterizes the companies actions as a violation of 
the racketeer influenced and corrupt organizations act and asks for 
unspecified damages 
also named in the 12count suit are bolars president robert 
shulman and port washington nybased schein pharmaceutical 
inc the company that developed marketed and sold bolars version 
an assistant to bolars general counsel who did not give her 
name said she could not comment on the suit late tuesday because 
the company had not received a copy of the complaint 
officials at vitarine did not return a message left at their 
offices tuesday afternoon 
smithkline beecham plc is the big pharmaceutical company formed 
last summer in the merger of smithkline beckman corp and britains 
beecham plc 
