<TEXT>
first world cheese inc with the help of the 
21 clubs chef introduced a line of fatfree lowcholesterol 
cheese wednesday described as the first of its kind to begin 
national distribution 
the small but fastgrowing firm hopes to expand on the success 
of its lowsalt and lowcholesterol cheeses sold under the pre 
monde alpine lace label 
we feel there is a small segment of the population who gave up 
cheese and dairy products due to health concerns said carl wolf 
first worlds president and chief executive officer the consumer 
is ready for this 
alpine lace lean n free cheeses will appeal to nutritionminded 
consumers keen to trim fat from their diets wolf said in remarks 
before lunch was served at the famous manhattan restaurant 
the menu featured dishes prepared with the fatfree cheese by 
the 21 clubs executive chef michael lomonaco the meal from 
the cheddar corn chowder to the cheddar stuffed peppers 
accompanying the main course drew favorable comments from diners 
however when eaten uncooked the cheeses lack the full flavor of 
their fatty cousins 
the new cheeses will be widely available in grocery stores 
around the country by july in american cheddar and mozzarella 
varieties prices will range from 189 for packages of shredded 
cheese to 499 per pound at the delicatessen counter 
the existing alpine lace brands are carried in about 30000 
retail outlets nationwide according to wolf alpine lace is the 
bestselling cheese brand at the countrys delis 
all three new varieties have about 35 calories in a oneounce 
serving they contain less than 05 gram of fat per serving 
compared with about six to nine grams in traditional cheeses a 
serving has about 5 milligrams of cholesterol vs about 20 to 30 
milligrams for regular american cheddar and mozzarella 
aly gamay who holds a doctorate in food science developed the 
fatfree cheese over years of trial and error working independently 
at a company he founded 
he told reporters that most skim milk cheeses taste like 
cardboard and thousands of his early formulations were no exception 
gamay an egyptian native who came to the united states 11 years 
ago said his wife sampled all his experiments and after thousands 
of taste tests screamed enough enough i cant take it 
anymore 
finally gamay said he arrived at a process that produced a 
tasty but lean cheese using skim milk cheese as a base the 
addition of enzymes and flavorings compensate for the absence of 
fat giving the cheese the smoothness and mouth feel that people 
expect 
gamays creation was test marketed under the cheese smart name 
in detroit charlotte nc and detroit sales were strong he 
said 
first world bought gamays cheese technology including three 
pending patents and cheese smart in may gamay said he will act as 
a consultant to first world and help develop new products 
wolf said first world eventually will bring out additional 
cheese varieties such as brie and gorgonzola in fatfree versions 
first world hopes to carve out a big slice of the growing market 
for socalled nutritional cheeses now running about 550 million a 
year at retail wolf said retail sales of these reduced calorie 
fat and cholesterol cheeses could grow to about 4 billion by the 
mid1990s 
by being the first to roll out its cheese nationally the 
maplewood njbased company has an advantage over its larger 
competitors who food industry analysts say are developing fatfree 
cheeses philip morris cos incs kraft division has been testing 
such a cheese in phoenix analysts said 
how does a food professional rate the taste and cooking 
properties of the new cheese 
chef lomonaco said it was easier to bake it into recipes than to 
broil it it worked well in soups muffins and even souffles and 
would make an excellent sauce he said 
as for taste lomonaco said its unrealistic to expect fatfree 
cheese to taste like its traditional counterpart it has its own 
unique good taste he said 
</TEXT>
