<TEXT>
john a mulheren jr took the stand at his 
securities fraud trial wednesday and denied making an illegal stock 
parking transaction with ivan boesky 
mulheren a former business associate of boesky said he balked 
when boeskys chief trader michael davidoff said boesky wanted to 
sell 330000 shares of unocal corp stock in 1985 with an agreement 
to buy it back at a later date 
mulheren said he told davidoff you can stop right there i 
dont do those trades 
mulheren also described his first meeting with boesky in 1976 at 
a dinner at an expensive manhattan restaurant dinner which had 
been arranged by stock speculator sandy lewis he said boesky 
ordered six to eight entrees and decided which one to eat after 
they arrived at the table 
he seemed like someone out of a movie mulheren said he 
seemed to be very smart a little outlandish 
boesky once one of wall streets most powerful stock 
speculators paid 100 million in penalties and pleaded guilty to 
one felony to settle wall streets biggest insider trading case 
ever in exchange he gave government investigators incriminating 
information about a number of his associates 
mulheren 40 is charged with 41 counts of conspiracy 
securities fraud mail fraud and recordkeeping violations 
involving his friendship with boesky 
he is accused of scheming with boesky to manipulate the stock 
price of gulf amp western inc and concealing the ownership of other 
stocks including unocal to help boesky cheat on his taxes and 
evade federal securities laws 
mulheren said he bought the unocal shares after his discussion 
with davidoff and sold them on the open market at a loss about 
three weeks later 
he said he had never agreed to sell the securities back to 
boesky or davidoff his account of the transaction contradicts 
previous testimony by key prosecution witnesses including boesky 
and davidoff 
mulheren who was known as a daring trader who wore jeans to the 
office carried over his casual style to the witness stand he wore 
an opennecked shirt sports pants and topsiders with no socks and 
often answered questions by his attorney thomas puccio by saying 
yeah 
puccio also elicited from mulheren that he has been diagnosed as 
manicdepressive and has taken the prescribed drug lithium as 
treatment 
prosecutors objected to the testimony but us district judge 
miriam cedarbaum allowed it as long as puccio did not use it to 
argue that the illness may have affected mulherens judgement 
in february 1988 police arrested mulheren leaving his rumson 
nj mansion with a loaded assault rifle according to court 
documents mulheren intended to shoot boesky because of his 
cooperation with prosecutors 
mulherens doctors later said the episode happened because 
mulheren had stopped taking lithium new jersey authorities dropped 
weapons possession charges in exchange for three years of probation 
mulheren was expected to continue his testimony thursday 
