companys technology 
hitachi and hewlettpackard also will jointly introduce 
development tools for the chip market and will share in hps 
precision architecture risc design information the companies said 
wednesday 
risc reduced instruction set computing is a design that 
increases the speed of chips by cutting down on the number of 
functions they perform 
last july the two companies agreed to develop jointly a new 
higherspeed risc chip set to be used in computer systems produced 
by both companies 
the new agreement strengthens the relationship and aims to 
promote wide acceptance of precision architecture risc 
hitachi said it expect to make the risc chips commercially 
available in the spring of 1991 and eventually will build a 
product line ranging from several millions of instructions per 
second to 100 or more mips 
</TEXT>
