<TEXT>
credit woes hit the west coast banking market 
wednesday as a leading rating agency downgraded security pacific 
corp and wells fargo corp citing worries over loans for 
takeovers and california commercial real estate 
the action by moodys investors service came just two days after 
the agency downgraded the debt of chase manhattan the nations 
second largest bank because of concerns about real estate lending 
in recent weeks moodys and standard amp poors corp have 
lowered their ratings on citicorp the nations biggest bank 
citing real estate and takeover loans 
moodys lowered its ratings on the longterm debt of security 
pacific and wells fargo by one notch the actions affected 32 
billion in debt of wells fargo and its subsidiaries and about 74 
billion at security pacific 
even after the move the debt has a solid investmentgrade 
rating 
the actions drew protests from the two companies whose main 
subsidiaries security pacific national bank and wells fargo bank 
are the second and thirdlargest banks in california and among the 
top ten in the nation 
moodys did not describe specific problem loans but said the 
california real estate market has only begun to soften both 
companies may have to beef up reserves against possible loan losses 
despite have diversified real estate portfolios and apparently 
sound underwriting standards moodys said 
both companies also have substantial exposure to highly 
leveraged transactions moodys said such transactions include 
corporate buyouts and recapitalizations 
we have maintained a wellbalanced loan portfolio consistent 
with the demands of the marketplace and with adequate and 
appropriate levels of reserves security pacific chief executive 
robert h smith said in a statement 
leslie altick wells fargo senior vice president for investor 
relations said wells fargo was not convinced california real 
estate is headed for new problems softness in the office building 
and hotel markets is already welldocumented but wells fargo 
believes californias underlying economy is too strong for a major 
downturn to occur she said 
moodys lowered its ratings on the two bank holding companys 
senior debt to singlea1 from doublea3 
